        <element name="Death Investigation" type="Archetype Feature" source="Martial Archetype Raven Knight" id="ID_KSM_MARK_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_RAVEN_KNIGHT_DEATH_INVESTIGATION">
            <description>
                <p></p>
                <p class="indent">When you choose this Archetype at 3rd level, you gain proficiency in the Investigation skill. Additionally, you can make Intelligence (Investigation) check with advantage when attempting to determine the cause of death of a creature.</p>
            </description>
            <sheet>
                <description></description>
            </sheet>
            <rules>
            </rules>
        </element>
        <element name="Soul Severing" type="Archetype Feature" source="Martial Archetype Raven Knight" id="ID_KSM_MARK_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_RAVEN_KNIGHT_SOUL_SEVERING">
            <description>
                <p></p>
                <p class="indent">At 3rd level, when you reduce a creature to 0 hitpoints you sever the connection of the creatures soul to its body. That creature cannot be turned into an undead for the next hour. Additionally, as a reaction, when a creature is reduced to 0 hit points within 15ft of you you can empower your weapon with that creatures souls energy. Your next weapon attack deals additional necrotic damage equal to half your fighter level plus your Constitution modifier. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Constitution modifier and regain all uses after finishing a long rest.</p>
            </description>
            <sheet>
                <description></description>
            </sheet>
            <rules>
            </rules>
        </element>
        <element name="Feather Step" type="Archetype Feature" source="Martial Archetype Raven Knight" id="ID_KSM_MARK_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_RAVEN_KNIGHT_FEATHER_STEP">
            <description>
                <p></p>
                <p class="indent">At 7th level, you move with the grace of the raven. Your walking speed increases by 10ft. Additionally, as a bonus action, you gain a flight speed equal to your walking speed until the end of your turn, if you end your in midair you drop to the ground.</p>
            </description>
            <sheet>
                <description></description>
            </sheet>
            <rules>
            </rules>
        </element>
        <element name="Door to the Shadowfell" type="Archetype Feature" source="Martial Archetype Raven Knight" id="ID_KSM_MARK_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_RAVEN_KNIGHT_DOOR_TO_THE_SHADOWFELL">
            <description>
                <p></p>
                <p class="indent">At 10th level, you can momentarily open a gateway to the Shadowfell and call forth some sorrowsworn. As an action, you summon a number of The Wretched equal to your proficiency modifier once per long rest. These creatures are under the charmed condition and after 1 minute they magically return to the Shadowfell. Additionally, you gain advantage when making weapon attacks against an undead creature.</p>
            </description>
            <sheet>
                <description></description>
            </sheet>
            <rules>
            </rules>
        </element>
        <element name="The Queens Blessing" type="Archetype Feature" source="Martial Archetype Raven Knight" id="ID_KSM_MARK_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_RAVEN_KNIGHT_THE_QUEENS_BLESSING">
            <description>
                <p></p>
                <p class="indent">At 15th level, the Raven Queen grants you a blessing. You gain advantage on death saving throws, immunity to the frightened condition, and resistance to necrotic damage.</p>
            </description>
            <sheet>
                <description></description>
            </sheet>
            <rules>
            </rules>
        </element>
        <element name="Duty even in Death" type="Archetype Feature" source="Martial Archetype Raven Knight" id="ID_KSM_MARK_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_RAVEN_KNIGHT_DUTY_EVEN_IN_DEATH">
            <description>
                <p></p>
                <p class="indent">At 18th level, when you are reduced to 0 hit points or a killed you can use your reaction have your spirit possess your body to avenge yourself. You can make a melee weapon attack against the creature that killed you and on a hit you critically hit that creature and regain hit points equal to the damage dealt. You can do this once per long rest.</p>
            </description>
            <sheet>
                <description></description>
            </sheet>
            <rules>
            </rules>
        </element>

